FBIS4-36639 "drnes113_j_94007" FBIS-NES-94-113 Daily Report 10 Jun 1994 ARABIAN PENINSULA Yemen Aden Forces Capture `Sophisticated' Communications System Aden Forces Capture `Sophisticated' Communications System EA1006172094 Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network in Arabic 1431 GMT 10 Jun 94 EA1006172094 Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network in Arabic 1431 GMT 10 Jun 94 Arabic BFN [Text] Honorable listeners: A responsible source at the Democratic Republic of Yemen Defense Ministry has stated that the popular resistance, in the center of Shu'ayb in al-Dali' Province, with rare heroism under the leadership of fighters from the war of liberation, yesterday repulsed attacks by the invaders of the bloody al-Ahmar gang, who were targeting citizens' villages and property. The source said, in a statement for the YEMENI NEWS AGENCY, Aden, that the popular resistance succeeded in repulsing enemy attacks, on whom they inflicted huge losses, including the destruction of a military crew [taqm]. They killed Staff Lieutenant Colonel Salih 'Ali Salih Zahir al-Sanhani, in whose possession they found a quantity of drugs and important documents. They also killed a number of enemy officers and men, and captured a sophisticated communications system.
